MERS-CoV, Saudi Arabia
----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 28 Jan 2016 from Mr Abdulghani Y. M. Al Fadhl, Director General, Animal and Plant Quarantine Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 29 Dec 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 20 Jan 2016
Reason for notification: Emerging disease
Morbidity: 2.36 percent
Mortality: 0 percent
Zoonotic impact: No
Causal agent: MERS-CoV

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Jeddah, Makkah
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Dec 2015
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Camelidae / 465 / 11 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Livestock market in Jeddah

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Camelidae / 2.37 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Screening; disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Veterinary Diagnostic Laboratory, Riyadh (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Camelidae / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 20 Jan 2016 / Positive
Camelidae / real-time reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 20 Jan 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

